				<br>
				<p><strong>Microgrid:</strong> is a a group of interconnected loads and distributed energy resources that acts as a single controllable entity with respect to the grid.
				</p>
				<p><strong>Renewable energy sources:</strong> are forms of energy derived from natural processes that are continuously replenished, such as sunlight, wind, rain, tides, and geothermal heat. 
					Unlike fossil fuels, they do not deplete over time and have minimal impact on the environment when harnessed correctly.
				</p>
				<p><strong>Electric Power: </strong>the rate at which electrical energy is transferred by an electric circuit. Measured in Watts (W).
				</p>
				<p><strong>Electric Energy: </strong>the energy which is caused by the movement of the electrons from one place to another. Measured in Watts an hour (Wh)
				</p>
